ocking attacks with it. You also get +0.5% chance per point of skill in Shield spec and the con of your shield vs. the mob has something to do with it as well. At level 40 with an orange Kite shield and 30 Shield spec, I block roughly 20-70% of the swings yellow-con mobs take at me, that’s not too bad(this is PvE, it’s tough to test things like this, 1 on 1, against players but it should hold relatively true in PvP as well).<br><br>There are a few added bonuses of wielding a shield and being able to specialize in it, most of all – Guard. Guard is the skill that allows you to take hits for another person in the party(I have no idea if it’s called Guard in non-Midgard realms), it’s a passive-defensive ability. You select a member to Guard and the skill gets checked anytime they get swung at and you're within range.<br><br>Here lies the key to Double Defense, all you need is two people in the group with Shield spec. You have one person be the primary tank, smacking the mob with only his taunt-building weapon skill to keep it on him. You have the other Shield spec having tank Guard him. Each swing that’s taken at the main tank will have two chances to be blocked, once by the tank and once by the person Guarding him. 2-3 hits blocked by a second person may not seem like much, but when they add up to 600+ damage it’s easy to see how this is a pretty solid tactic.<br><br>Actually, that’s the only one I can think of right now. Feel free to add on… <p><b>Vendrix</b><br><a href=http://www.dakor.net><font size=2>Da</a><a href=http://www.fatsex.com/tour>`</a><a href=http://www.dakor.net>Kor</font></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukanewilliam.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kanewilliam</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#E9D756>(11/20/01 6:55:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tips, tricks and sploits!</span><hr size=1> That Guard ability is Protect in Albion.. I to use it on my cleric. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uelwyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elwyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 586<br> <font color=#E9D756>(11/20/01 7:43:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tips, tricks and sploits!</span><hr size=1> Don't think its the same thing.  Midgard has protect also.<br>I think guard is a shield-specific skill. <p><br><br><b>Elwyn<a href="http://www.dakor.net">-= Da`Kor =-</a></b><br><i><font size =-1>And I will strike down upon thee with great vengeance and furious anger those who attempt to poison and destroy my brothers</font></i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukizmetbayashi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kizmet Bayashi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 363<br> <font color=#E9D756>(11/20/01 9:15:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tips, tricks and sploits!</span><hr size=1> Protect in Midgard is used on casters to distract the mob when the caster casts. I dont know the specifics on how it works.<br><br>Kizmet<br>39 Troll Warrior Midgard<br>Da`Kor <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uwantonsunderforge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wanton Sunderforge</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#E9D756>(11/20/01 9:27:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tips, tricks and sploits!</span><hr size=1> Protect is a taunt to lessen the aggro of a specific group member. I.E. Healer1 casts heal, his aggro is reduced and given to you. Protect and Provoking is an easy way for a thane to keep aggro. This doesn't require a shield to use so you can use a nice Dull Asterite or Twilight 2H and go to work.<br><br>Guard will only work if you're failry close to the &quot;Guarded&quot; group member. Much like Intercept except you dont' have to refresh it every 5 minutes.<br> <p>Wanton Sunderforge <br>Dwarven Thane of Thor<br>Bedevere, Midgard Realm<br>Galactic Overlord of <a href="http://www.ordered-chaos.com">Ordered Chaos</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uthebudan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thebudan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 106<br> <font color=#E9D756>(11/20/01 12:29:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tips, tricks and sploits!</span><hr size=1> The Hibernian equivalent to guard is 'Intercept'.  It works exactly as Vendrix describes - allowing you to intercept attack(s) intended for a chosen groupmate.<br><br>It works well against melees, but since you have to be fairly close to your chosen groupmate to intercept, you have to watch out for caster types that like to drop AE stuff if you are bunched together.<br><br>Broc - Hero/Palomides<br><br>Budan Sorcerer/Isuelt<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uarikel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arikel</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1904<br> <font color=#E9D756>(11/20/01 12:29:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tips, tricks and sploits!</span><hr size=1> Protect and guard are the same across the realms. <p>Ahry - hero of Gaoth an Iar, Percival server <BR>Arikel Callistrae - retiredmonk of the Erollisi Marr server</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umalqanar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Malqanar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 205<br> <font color=#E9D756>(11/20/01 12:29:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tips, tricks and sploits!</span><hr size=1> Shields only work if the mob/player is in front of you.. Something to remember in PvP <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uvendrix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vendrix</A></span><br> <sp